de.esoco.lib.json

Class JsonObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.obrel.core.RelatedObject
      • de.esoco.lib.json.JsonObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JsonSerializable<JsonObject>, Relatable

    public class JsonObject
extends RelatedObject
implements JsonSerializable<JsonObject>
    A generic JSON object that provides access methods for JSON datatypes.

      • fromJson

        public JsonObject fromJson(java.lang.String sJson)
        Parses data from a JSON string and returns the resulting instance. Invocations should always work with the returned instance as immutable implementations will return a new instance.

        All implementing types should provide a no-argument constructor that does as few initialization as possible. This applies especially to immutable types that will only be created to invoke this method, which will then create and fill a new instance.

        Specified by:
        fromJson in interface JsonSerializable<JsonObject>
        Parameters:
        sJson - The JSON string to parse
        Returns:
        This instance so that it can be directly used after de-serialization

      • getInt

        public int getInt(java.lang.String sName,
                  int nDefault)
        Returns a property value as an integer or a default value if the property is not set or NULL. If the property value is a Number it's int value will be returned. If it is a string it will be tried to parse it into an int which will throw an exception on parsing errors. Else the default value will be returned. If the number exceeds the value range of an int truncation or exceptions may occur.
        Parameters:
        sName - The property name
        nDefault - The default value if the property is NULL
        Returns:
        The integer value
        Throws:
        java.lang.ClassCastException - If the property is not a number
